      • ProtectedRegion

        public ProtectedRegion(String zoneName,
                       String enterMessage,
                       String worldName,
                       int xOne,
                       int yOne,
                       int zOne,
                       int xTwo,
                       int yTwo,
                       int zTwo,
                       String lfString)
        General constructor, used to recreate regions from database entries.
        Parameters:
        zoneName - The name of the Protected Region.
        enterMessage - The message displayed when a player tries to type a /tpp [dogs/cats/birds] command in the region. This supports &[#] color codes.
        worldName - The name of the world the Protected Region is in.
        xOne - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point's X location.
        yOne - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point's Y location.
        zOne - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point's Z location.
        xTwo - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point's X location.
        yTwo - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point's Y location.
        zTwo - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the maximum point's Z location.
        lfString - A string representing the LostAndFound Region to be linked to this ProtectedRegion.

        General constructor, uses Location objects to represent the maximum and minimum of the cube.
        Parameters:
        zoneName - The name of the Protected Region.
        enterMessage - The message displayed when a player tries to type a /tpp [dogs/cats/birds] command in the region. This supports &[#] color codes.
        worldName - The name of the world the Protected Region is in.
        world - A world reference representing the world where the Protected Region is in.
        minLoc - The Protected Region is generated based on two points: the minimum and maximum of the cube. This is the minimum point.

        lfString - A string representing the LostAndFound Region to be linked to this ProtectedRegion.
